  "doc_id": "41667",
  "text": "Boundary conditions were determined as a constant inlet pressure of p in = 12,621 Pa, and an outlet pressure of p out = 12,491 Pa in the arterial tree. The inlet value was adapted from the mean pressure in the human renal artery, equivalent to 12,799 Pa (96 mmHg) according to the literature. [CITATION_1] The outlet pressure was deliberately defined according to Ufendahl et al.'s 39 statement that the pressure drop up to the arcuate arteries was negligible. The pressure drop was assumed to be about 1.6%. For the venous tree the inlet pressure p in was set at 740 Pa and the outlet pressure, p out , at 547 Pa.",
